[[sn:Shirahige Bridge]] [[ja:白鬚橋]]
<!--Shirahige Bridge--><!--Shirahige Bridge--><!--Shirahige Bridge--><!--Shirahige Bridge--><!--Shirahige Bridge--><!--Shirahige Bridge-->

[[File:Shirahige bashi.jpg|thumb|200px|From Arakawa Ward, Tokyo (January 2008)]] {{Ja_Pref_Route_Sign|pref=Tokyo|number=306|align=left}} [[File:Shirahigebashi-sundown-side-april28-2015.jpg|thumb|200px|From Sumida Ward, Tokyo (April 2015)]] [[File:Shirahigebashi-fromskytree-2016 4 9.jpg|thumb|200px|From Tokyo Skytree (April 2016)]]
'''Shirahige Bridge''' (白鬚橋, ''Shirahige-bashi'') is a bridge spanning the {{ill|Sumida River|ja|隅田川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sumida River|qq=}}, carrying the {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 306|ja|東京都道306号王子千住夢の島線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo Metropolitan Route 306|qq=}} (commonly known as Meiji-dōri). The western bank separates {{ill|Minami-Senju|ja|南千住|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minami-Senju|qq=}}, Arakawa Ward, from {{ill|Hashiba|ja|橋場|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hashiba|qq=}}, Taitō Ward, while the eastern bank divides {{ill|Tsuijidō|ja|堤通|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuijidō|qq=}} 1 and 2-chōme in Sumida Ward. The bridge takes its name from the nearby {{ill|Shirahige Shrine|ja|白鬚神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shirahige Shrine|qq=}}. Note that the correct kanji for the name is "鬚" (chin whiskers), often mistakenly written as "髭" (moustache).
== History == The bridge was first constructed in May 1914 (Taishō 3). Local residents raised funds to establish the Shirahige Bridge Corporation, beginning construction in April 1913 (Taishō 2). The wooden bridge was completed within a year, measuring approximately 130 ken (about 230 meters) in length. A toll of one sen per person was charged<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|title=The History of the Sumida River as Seen from Its Bridges|author=飯田雅男|publisher=Bungeisha|date=2002-06|page=212|isbn=4-8355-3894-3}}</ref>, but competition from ferry services made it challenging to maintain operations. Despite doubling the toll to two sen, the company struggled to maintain the bridge, eventually selling it to Tokyo Prefecture in 1925 (Taishō 14).
Although it suffered no damage during the {{ill|1923 Great Kantō Earthquake|ja|関東大震災|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1923 Great Kantō Earthquake|qq=}}, the urban planning project for the city's first-class ring road (Route No. 16, now Meiji-dōri) necessitated replacing the wooden bridge with the current iron bridge.<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Bridges of Sumida River|publisher=Sumida Ward Green Library|date=1993-03|series=Sumida Ward Library Series 8|page=61}}</ref>
The location was originally home to the "{{ill|Hashiba Ferry|ja|橋場の渡し|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hashiba Ferry|qq=}}" and "{{ill|Shirahige Ferry|ja|白鬚の渡し|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shirahige Ferry|qq=}}," with Hashiba Ferry serving as a primary crossing point on the Sumida River during the Edo period until the construction of {{ill|Senju Bridge|ja|千住大橋|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senju Bridge|qq=}} in Bunroku 3 (1594). The famous "Kototoi no Uta" poem from the {{ill|Tales of Ise|ja|伊勢物語|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tales of Ise|qq=}}, attributed to {{ill|Ariwara no Narihira|ja|在原業平|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ariwara no Narihira|qq=}}, was composed at this crossing.
== Bridge Specifications == * '''Structure type''': Through-arch braced ribbed bridge * '''Length''': 167.6 meters<ref name=":0" /> * '''Width''': 24.1 meters<ref name=":0" /> * '''Steel weight''': 1,923 tons<ref name=":0" /> * '''Construction started''': Shōwa 3 (1928) July<ref name=":0" /> * '''Completed''': Shōwa 6 (1931) June<ref name=":0" /> * '''Contractor''': Tokyo Prefecture * '''Designer''': {{ill|Jun Masuda|ja|増田淳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jun Masuda|qq=}} * '''Bridge girder manufacturer''': Kawasaki Dockyard * '''Similar design''': {{ill|Asahi Bridge (Asahikawa)|ja|旭橋 (旭川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asahi Bridge (Asahikawa)|qq=}}
== Public Transportation == * '''{{ill|Toei Bus|ja|都営バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toei Bus|qq=}}''' ** {{ill|Route 22|ja|都営バス南千住営業所#里22系統|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Route 22|qq=}}: {{ill|Ni11ori Station|ja|日暮里駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ni11ori Station|qq=}} - {{ill|Mikawashima Station|ja|三河島駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikawashima Station|qq=}} - {{ill|Arakawa Ward Office|ja|荒川区役所|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arakawa Ward Office|qq=}} - Namidabashi - Hashiba 2-chōme - Higashi Mukōjima Hirokōji - {{ill|Kameido Station|ja|亀戸駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kameido Station|qq=}}
